This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney on Air Force One en route to Toledo, Ohio. Carney gives an update on President Obama's upcoming visit to Louisiana, where he will tour flood damage caused by Hurricane Isaac. He also mentions the early voting and voting by mail statistics in Colorado, Ohio, and Iowa. The article includes a discussion on the President's preparations for the upcoming convention and the importance of presenting a forward-looking agenda. Carney clarifies the President's plan for Afghanistan and reiterates the United States' commitment to preventing Iran from acquiring a nuclear weapon. The press gaggle ends with a lighthearted discussion about the Washington Nationals and pitcher Stephen Strasburg.